<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4668906>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 2. (A–C) Pseudomonocelis caribbea sp. n.: (A) copulatory organ; (B) female genital organs; (C) spermatogonial mitosis. (D–G) P. ophiocephala, spermatogonial mitoses from different populations: (D) CAL; (E) HAI; (F) MLK; (G) OCC. (H, I) P. cf. caυernicola: live animals showing cephalic pigmentation. (L) P. pardii: section of the female genital region at the ‘‘horizontal canal’’ level. See text for abbreviations. Scale bar: 5 Mm (C–G); 10 Mm (A, B, H, L); 100 Mm (I)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4668906/files/figure.png" .

